{"name":"Mathlib.Topology.Sheaves.SheafCondition.UniqueGluing","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Topology.Sheaves.Forget","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Limits.Shapes.Types","Mathlib.Topology.Sheaves.Sheaf","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Types"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.lean#L312-L325","name":"TopCat.Sheaf.eq_of_locally_eq₂","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.html#TopCat.Sheaf.eq_of_locally_eq₂","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.lean#L298-L308","name":"TopCat.Sheaf.eq_of_locally_eq'","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.html#TopCat.Sheaf.eq_of_locally_eq'","doc":"In this version of the lemma, the inclusion homs `iUV` can be specified directly by the user,\nwhich can be more convenient in practice.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.lean#L276-L291","name":"TopCat.Sheaf.eq_of_locally_eq","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.html#TopCat.Sheaf.eq_of_locally_eq","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.lean#L258-L271","name":"TopCat.Sheaf.existsUnique_gluing'","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.html#TopCat.Sheaf.existsUnique_gluing'","doc":"In this version of the lemma, the inclusion homs `iUV` can be specified directly by the user,\nwhich can be more convenient in practice.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.lean#L249-L251","name":"TopCat.Sheaf.existsUnique_gluing","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.html#TopCat.Sheaf.existsUnique_gluing","doc":"A more convenient way of obtaining a unique gluing of sections for a sheaf.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.lean#L221-L223","name":"TopCat.Presheaf.isSheaf_iff_isSheafUniqueGluing","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.html#TopCat.Presheaf.isSheaf_iff_isSheafUniqueGluing","doc":"For presheaves valued in a concrete category, whose forgetful functor reflects isomorphisms and\npreserves limits, the sheaf condition in terms of unique gluings is equivalent to the usual one\nin terms of equalizer diagrams.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.lean#L202-L203","name":"TopCat.Presheaf.isSheaf_iff_isSheafUniqueGluing_types","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.html#TopCat.Presheaf.isSheaf_iff_isSheafUniqueGluing_types","doc":"For type-valued presheaves, the sheaf condition in terms of unique gluings is equivalent to the\nusual sheaf condition in terms of equalizer diagrams.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.lean#L179-L195","name":"TopCat.Presheaf.isSheafUniqueGluing_of_isSheaf_types","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.html#TopCat.Presheaf.isSheafUniqueGluing_of_isSheaf_types","doc":"The sheaf condition in terms of unique gluings can be obtained from the usual\n\"equalizer\" sheaf condition.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.lean#L150-L172","name":"TopCat.Presheaf.isSheaf_of_isSheafUniqueGluing_types","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.html#TopCat.Presheaf.isSheaf_of_isSheafUniqueGluing_types","doc":"The \"equalizer\" sheaf condition can be obtained from the sheaf condition\nin terms of unique gluings.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.lean#L133-L143","name":"TopCat.Presheaf.isGluing_iff_eq_res","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.html#TopCat.Presheaf.isGluing_iff_eq_res","doc":"Under the isomorphism `piOpensIsoSectionsFamily`, being a gluing of a family of\nsections `sf` is the same as lying in the preimage of `res` (the leftmost arrow of the\nequalizer diagram).\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.lean#L110-L124","name":"TopCat.Presheaf.compatible_iff_leftRes_eq_rightRes","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.html#TopCat.Presheaf.compatible_iff_leftRes_eq_rightRes","doc":"Under the isomorphism `piOpensIsoSectionsFamily`, compatibility of sections is the same\nas being equalized by the arrows `leftRes` and `rightRes` of the equalizer diagram.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.lean#L100-L103","name":"TopCat.Presheaf.piOpensIsoSectionsFamily","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.html#TopCat.Presheaf.piOpensIsoSectionsFamily","doc":"For presheaves of types, terms of `piOpens F U` are just families of sections.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.lean#L86-L88","name":"TopCat.Presheaf.IsSheafUniqueGluing","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.html#TopCat.Presheaf.IsSheafUniqueGluing","doc":"The sheaf condition in terms of unique gluings. A presheaf `F : presheaf C X` satisfies this sheaf\ncondition if and only if, for every compatible family of sections `sf : Π i : ι, F.obj (op (U i))`,\nthere exists a unique gluing `s : F.obj (op (supr U))`.\n\nWe prove this to be equivalent to the usual one below in\n`TopCat.Presheaf.isSheaf_iff_isSheafUniqueGluing`\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.lean#L73-L74","name":"TopCat.Presheaf.IsGluing","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.html#TopCat.Presheaf.IsGluing","doc":"A section `s` is a gluing for a family of sections `sf` if it restricts to `sf i` on `U i`,\nfor all `i`\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.lean#L65-L66","name":"TopCat.Presheaf.IsCompatible","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/SheafCondition/UniqueGluing.html#TopCat.Presheaf.IsCompatible","doc":"A family of sections `sf` is compatible, if the restrictions of `sf i` and `sf j` to `U i ⊓ U j`\nagree, for all `i` and `j`\n"}]}